Information

MY SUGAR CAT is Nakashima Mika's 19th single. It follows the same themes as CRY NO MORE and ALL HANDS TOGETHER do, but has a more summery feel to it. This song is also influenced by blues and reggae. MY SUGAR CAT was used as the Kanebo KATE CM song. The coupling track, Koishikute, is a BEGIN cover. The first press of this single featured a picture label disc. The single reached #14 on Oricon and charted for five weeks selling a total of 19,120 units.

Disambiguation

There are two known versions of MY SUGAR CAT to be included in Mika's discography. These include:

MY SUGAR CAT

Found on the MY SUGAR CAT single as track one. This is the version set to the PV.

MY SUGAR CAT (Instrumental)

Found on the MY SUGAR CAT single as track three. This version is the standard version, except without the main vocals.
